toxicology, and epidemiology of talc and related products. The principal focus will be on the latest toxicologic
and epidemiologic studies, particularly as they reflect on the safe uses of talc in consumer products.
The following topic areas will be discussed: (1) Characteristics of cosmetic-grade talc; (2) a history of the uses
of talc in a variety of consumer products; (3) current quality control measures to insure safety; (4) the regulatory
history of talc; (5) recent National Toxicology Program studies of chronic pulmonary exposure of rodents to talc
and the relevance of these studies to human risk assessment; and (6) the significance of contrasting epidemiologic
studies of talc exposure. 
