Able to be linked to each other; and 

Readily accessible to police, courts, and planners.



E. Evaluation



States should evaluate all impaired driving system activities regularly to ensure that programs are effective and
scarce resources are allocated appropriately. Evaluation should be:






Included in initial program planning to ensure that appropriate data are available and that adequate resources are
allocated;

Designed to use available traffic records systems effectively; and

Conducted regularly.






